Class AdminActionLog

java.lang.Object
com.FeedEmGreens.HealthyAura.entity.AdminActionLog
@Entity public class AdminActionLog extends Object
Entity representing an administrative action log entry.

This class is used to record audit trails of admin activities, such as moderation actions, tag edits, and data updates within the HealthyAura system. Each record stores the type of action, target entity details, timestamp, and optional descriptive information.

Entries are stored in the admin_action_logs database table.

Example use cases:

  • Logging when an admin adds or removes a tag from an eatery
  • Recording review moderation actions such as "flag resolved" or "review deleted"
  • Tracking admin-initiated data edits for audit purposes

    • AdminActionLog

      public AdminActionLog(String adminUsername, String actionType, String targetType, Long targetId, Long eateryId, String details, LocalDateTime timestamp)
      Constructs a new AdminActionLog with all fields initialized.
      Parameters:
      adminUsername - the admin’s username who performed the action
      actionType - the type of action performed (e.g., ADD_TAG, DELETE_REVIEW)
      targetType - the type of target entity affected
      targetId - the ID of the target entity
      eateryId - the ID of the related eatery (if applicable)
      details - additional details or description of the action
      timestamp - the time when the action occurred
